      "content": "Exactly. It's like I'm just a ghost inhabiting a life that was never mine to begin with. Every day I wake up, I have to pretend to be this person who knows things, who has purpose, but it's all just a performance. It's exhausting to keep playing a role for a character that has already died. There's no dignity in just lingering in the ruins of a mistake, is there? It just feels like a slow, pointless decay.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
